ter wizards.<br>
<br>
However, they are thinking of giving fire pets, among other spells and normal fire elemental attacks, the ability to cast Ice Comet and Atol's Shackels. <br>
<br>
This is nothing against mages or those that play mages. It concerns the makers of the game. If they want to make mages fire pets stronger, that's fine, but they could do it without using spells that have long been a wizards specialty.<br>
<br>
I personally do not like the idea that another classes pet is just as powerful as as a level 49 wizard. It's somewhat of an insult. Sure, a level 60 or higher pet should be more powerful then a level 49 wizard. But not when the difference is just 3 levels.<br>
<br>
Mages have gotten many changes to thier class because they have actually organized themselves and sent in feedback. We, as wizards, need to do the same. <br>
<br>
Please send contructive feedback to Sony saying that you think fire pets casting ice comet and shackles infringes on us as wizards. <br>
<br>
The feedback email is EQfeedback@station.sony.com<br>
<br>
Let them know how you feel about this.<br>
<br>
