<br>
They did cast the following spells <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>before</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<br>
° Tishan's Clash <br>
° Root <br>
° Dispell Magic <br>
° Flame shock <br>
° Shielding <br>
° O'Keils Embers <br>
° Shield skin <br>
<br>
You may add some very bad melee skill if you want to (not that any sane mage ever used the Fire Pet for melee purpose). As you can see - clearly spells every group and raid loves to have randomly cast on mobs (especially Root and Dispell Magic) /sarcasm off . This pet existed for years now and was NEVER fixed or looked at.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now on Test the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Lvl 63 Fire Pet</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is casting:<br>
<br>
° Tishans Discord <br>
° Ice Comet <br>
° Atol's Spectral Shackels <br>
° Pillar of Frost  <br>
° Rend <br>
° Draught of Fire <br>
° Root  <br>
° Diamond Skin <br>
° Arch Shielding  <br>
° O'keils Flickering Flame <br>
° Fire elemental aura <br>
<br>
Now before the complaints are starting: Mages cannot control what spell a fire pet is casting. They choose spells rather randomly and have a limited mana pool. Let´s take a closer look at the spells: <br>
<br>
- Does a Mage want a pet to cast Root randomly? No, because it ***** up positioning and tanking in general. <br>
- Does a group (or raids) want Wizards and Mages cast AE spells on raids when you´re standing close to a wall (especially in PoP *g*) and there´s nothing to AE? No, because you might have some lovely mobs in camp soon.<br>
<br>
That leaves us with a few useless spells (Fire Elemental Aura, O´Keils) and a few more Wizard specific useful Damage Spells. If we now take a look at the old Pets and the new Pets *i* - as a mage - finally see a improvement. After 2 years of having a useless Fire Pet, i might now use this pet for groups (in outdoor zones with no possible adds near), but certainly not on raids (AE and Root? No thanks).<br>
<br>
Oh, keep in mind that these Fire Pets have a rather small Mana Pool. <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Now if you bring up Chain Casting i have a good way for SOE to prevent this: Add a 2-3 minutes <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Recast time</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Bingo, problem solved.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
